projects.name: Pop-Up Books

steps.instruction: Take two 9 x 12 pieces of construction paper and fold them in half. Now take one paper and find a dot in the middle of the folded edge.
Draw a line from the marked dot to the outer edge of the paper.
Using scissors, cut along the line, starting from the folded edge. Fold back the cut to create two triangles. Fold them back so they form two triangles.
steps.visual_description: Two triangles formed by cutting and folding.

steps.instruction: Open the cut again and also open the entire page. Now, hold the paper in such a way that it looks like a tent. Place your finger on the top of the triangle and carefully push it down so that the triangle is pushed through to the other side of the paper.
steps.visual_description: Paper held like a tent, with a triangle being pushed through.

steps.instruction: Now place your finger on the bottom of the paper triangle and repeat the same process. You will see that the top and bottom triangles will be pushed out to form a mouth inside the card.
steps.visual_description: Top and bottom triangles pushed out to form a mouth shape.

projects.finished_product_description: A pop-up book with a mouth-like mechanism.

diagram_descriptions: A close-up image of a pop-up book page featuring koala bears and foliage, made from layered brown and tan paper.

projects.name: Pop Up 90 degrees

steps.instruction: Each time you open or close the card, the mouth will open and close simultaneously and it will appear to be talking.

Now you can draw a person or animal or even a monster around the mouth and glue the inside and outside pages together. But make sure you do not apply glue in the area with the pop-up mouth. Your cover for your book is ready.
Now you can add pages to cover yours. Decide how many pages you want to include and fold each paper into sections. Glue inside the edges of the folded paper and attach the pages together. Let dry.
Choose the story and draw it on these pages, only when they are well dried. While writing the story on the inner pages, you can leave space to add pop-up characters.
Now cut out interesting characters for your story and determine which characters will be inserted on each page. Make sure to leave some space at the bottom of the characters.

Carefully glue the characters into the story. Make sure you fold the bottom of each character and then add a little glue on top of it. Press them firmly so they can stay in place properly. Continue the process for other characters on other pages of this book.

projects.name: Our Story Photo Album

steps.instruction: Take the 12x12 inch red cardstock and score a line down the center, dividing it into two 6x12 inch panels. Fold the cardstock in half along the score line to create the album base.
steps.visual_description: A hand holding a red cardstock, showing it folded in half.

steps.instruction: Cut the two sheets of 6x12 inch striped paper in half to create four 6x6 inch pieces. These will be used for the inner pages of the album.
steps.visual_description: A box filled with red and white striped paper, with a hand reaching in.

steps.instruction: Cut the 12x12 inch decorative paper to fit the front and back covers of the album. The dimensions will depend on the exact size of the folded album base.
steps.visual_description: A decorative paper box with text and patterns, with a hand holding its edge.

steps.instruction: Adhere the decorative paper to the front and back covers of the album. Then, adhere the striped paper pages inside the album.
steps.visual_description: A finished photo album cover with the title 'Our Story'.

steps.instruction: Add photos and embellishments to personalize the album.
steps.visual_description: A close-up of a finished photo album page with text 'Happy Anniversary 1st year Mel Vinka I LOVE YOU FOR A THOUSAND YEARS 21022012-21022013'.

tips: Use a strong adhesive for the covers.
Consider using different sizes of photos for visual interest.
